Overview

This lab focused on managing file and folder permissions in Windows using graphical tools and the command line. I practiced identifying effective permissions, modifying ACLs, and troubleshooting access issues â€” core tasks for IT Support, SysAdmin, and Security Operations roles.

 Objectives

By the end of this lab, I was able to:

View and interpret NTFS permissions

Modify user and group access rights

Create and assign new permissions

Remove or deny permissions when needed

Use RDP to access the lab environment

Understand inheritance and effective permissions

 Tools & Technologies

Windows Server (RDP session)

File Explorer Security tab

NTFS permissions

ACL Management

Command line basics

